UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1802
1 AN ACT relating to the Athletic Trainer Compact.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 311 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 ATHLETIC TRAINER COMPACT
6 SECTION 1. TITLE AND PURPOSE
7 This statute shall be known and cited as the Athletic Trainer Compact. The
8 purposes of this compact are to expand mobility of athletic training practice and
9 improve public access to services by providing qualified licensed athletic trainers the
10 ability to practice in other member states. This compact preserves the regulatory
11 authority of states to protect public health and safety through the current system of
12 state licensure.
13 This compact is designed to achieve the following objectives:
14 A. Increase public access to athletic training and enhance continuity of care by
15 providing for the mutual recognition of other licenses issued by member states;
16 B. Provide an additional streamlined opportunity for interstate practice by
17 licensed athletic trainers who meet compact uniform requirements;
18 C. Promote mobility and workforce development by eliminating the necessity
19 for licenses in multiple states by providing for the mutual recognition of other licenses
20 issued by member states;
21 D. Reduce administrative burdens on licensed athletic trainers and member
22 states;
23 E. Enhance the states’ ability to protect the public’s health and safety;
24 F. Encourage the cooperation of member states in regulating interstate
25 practice of licensed athletic trainers;
26 G. Support relocating active military members and their spouses;
27 H. Enhance the exchange of licensure, investigative, and disciplinary
Page 1 of 32
XXXX 2/10/2026 12:57 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1802
1 information among member states;
2 I. Allow for the use of telehealth to facilitate increased access to athletic
3 training services;
4 J. Support the uniformity of licensed athletic trainer licensure requirements
5 throughout the states;
6 K. Affirm the authority of all member states to hold a licensed athletic trainer
7 accountable for abiding by the scope of practice in the state in which the patient is
8 located at the time of care; and
9 L. Require adherence to the model compact language in order to promote
10 uniformity and ensure that all member states have accepted and are mutually obligated
11 to the same terms.
12 SECTION 2. DEFINITIONS
13 As used in this compact, unless the context requires otherwise, the following
14 definitions shall apply:
15 A. "Active Military Member" means any individual with full-time duty status
16 in the active armed forces of the United States, including members of the National
17 Guard and Reserve.
18 B. "Adverse Action" means any administrative, civil, equitable or criminal
19 action permitted by a state’s laws which is imposed by a licensing authority or other
20 authority against a licensee, including actions against an individual’s license or
21 compact privilege such as revocation, suspension, probation, monitoring of the
22 licensee, limitation on the licensee’s practice, or any other encumbrance on licensure
23 affecting a licensee’s authorization to practice.
24 C. "Alternative Program" means a non-disciplinary monitoring or practice
25 remediation process applicable to an athletic trainer approved by a state licensing
26 authority of a member state in which the athletic trainer is licensed. This includes, but
27 is not limited to, programs to which licensees with substance use, addiction, or mental
Page 2 of 32
XXXX 2/10/2026 12:57 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1802
1 health conditions are referred in lieu of adverse action.
2 D. "Athletic Training" means the prevention, examination, assessment,
3 treatment and rehabilitation of emergent, acute, or chronic injuries and medical
4 conditions as defined by applicable member state laws and regulations.
5 E. "Athletic Trainer Compact Commission" or "Compact Commission"
6 means the government agency whose membership consists of all states that have
7 enacted this compact, as described herein and which shall operate as an
8 instrumentality of the member states to administer and implement the compact
9 according to its terms.
10 F. "BOC" means the Board of Certification, Inc. or any successor
11 organization thereto.
12 G. "CAATE" means the Commission on Accreditation of Athletic Training
13 Education or any successor organization thereto.
14 H. "Charter Member State" means any member state which enacted and made
15 effective this compact by law before the compact effective date specified herein.
16 I. "Commissioner" means the individual appointed by a member state to serve
17 as the member of the commission for that member state.
18 J. "Compact Privilege" means the legal authorization granted by a remote
19 state, equivalent to a license, allowing a licensee from another member state to provide
20 athletic training services in a remote state.
21 K. "Compact Qualifying License" means a license that is not an encumbered
22 license issued by a member state to practice athletic training which qualifies the
23 licensee to exercise a compact privilege pursuant to Section 4 of this compact.
24 L. "Continuing Competence" means a requirement, as a condition of license
25 renewal, to provide evidence of successful participation, and completion of,
26 educational and professional activities relevant to practice or area of work. For
27 purposes of this compact, evidence of active BOC certification may satisfy the meaning
Page 3 of 32
