1 of continuing competence as set forth herein.
2 M. "Current Significant Investigative Information" means the existence of:
3 1. Investigative information that a licensing authority, after a preliminary
4 inquiry that includes notification and an opportunity for the subject licensee to
5 respond, if required by state law, has reason to believe is not groundless and, if proven
6 true, would indicate more than a minor infraction; or
7 2. Investigative information that indicates that the subject licensee represents
8 an immediate threat to public health and safety regardless of whether the subject
9 licensee has been notified and had an opportunity to respond.
10 N. "Criminal Background Check" means the submission of fingerprints or
11 other biometric-based information for a license applicant for the purpose of obtaining
12 that applicant’s criminal history record information, as defined in 28 C.F.R. § 20.3(d)
13 from the Federal Bureau of Investigation and the state’s criminal history record
14 repository as defined in 28 C.F.R. § 20.3(f).
15 O. "Data System" means the commission’s repository of information about
16 licensees, including but not limited to examination, licensure, investigative, compact
17 privilege, adverse action, and alternative program.
18 P. "Encumbrance" or "Encumbered" means a revocation or suspension of, or
19 any limitation or condition on, the full and unrestricted practice of athletic training.
20 Q. "Executive Committee" means a group of commissioners elected or
21 appointed to act on behalf of, and within the powers granted to them by, the compact
22 and commission.
23 R. "Investigative Information" means information, records, and documents
24 received or generated by a licensing authority pursuant to an investigation.
25 S. "Jurisprudence Requirement" means the assessment of an individual’s
26 knowledge of the laws and rules governing the practice of athletic training, as
27 applicable, in a state.
