6 SECTION 3. STATE PARTICIPATION IN THE COMPACT
7 A. To be eligible to join this compact and to maintain eligibility as a member
8 state, a state must:
9 1. Enact and maintain a statute that is not materially different from the model
10 compact language;
11 2. License and regulate the practice of athletic training;
12 3. Require that licensees in that state maintain continuing competence
13 standards as part of their state practice act or rules;
14 4. Have a mechanism in place for receiving and investigating complaints
15 about licensees;
16 5. Grant the compact privilege to a licensee who meets all the requirements
17 outlined in Section 4 in accordance with the terms of the compact and any rules
18 promulgated thereunder;
19 6. Participate fully in the compact commission’s data system, including using
20 the unique identifier as defined in rules;
21 7. Notify the compact commission, in compliance with the terms of the
22 compact and rules, of any adverse action or the availability of current significant
23 investigative information regarding a licensee;
24 8. Within a time frame established by rule, implement or utilize procedures for
25 considering the criminal history records of applicants for a compact qualifying license
26 which includes receiving the results of the Federal Bureau of Investigation record
27 search and shall use those results in making licensure decisions. These procedures
Page 6 of 32
XXXX 2/10/2026 12:57 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1802
1 shall include the submission of fingerprints or other biometric-based information by
2 applicants for the purpose of obtaining an applicant’s criminal history record
3 information from the Federal Bureau of Investigation and the agency responsible for
4 retaining that state’s criminal records; and
5 a. A member state must fully implement a criminal background check
6 requirement in order to participate in the issuance and acceptance of compact
7 privileges.
8 b. Communication between a member state and the compact commission or
9 among member states regarding the verification of eligibility for licensure through the
10 compact shall not include any information received from the Federal Bureau of
11 Investigation relating to a federal criminal records check performed by a member state.
12 9. Comply with and enforce the rules of the compact commission.
13 B. Member states may set and collect a fee for issuance and renewal of a
14 compact privilege to applicants.
15 C. Individuals without a compact qualifying license shall continue to be able to
16 apply for a member state’s single-state license as provided under the laws of each
17 member state.
18 D. Nothing in this compact shall affect the requirements established by a
19 member state for the issuance of a single state license.
20 E. A compact qualifying license shall be recognized by each remote state as
21 authorizing that licensee to engage in the practice of athletic training, under a compact
22 privilege, in another member state in accordance with the requirements in Section 4.
23 SECTION 4. COMPACT PRIVILEGE
24 A. To be eligible for a compact privilege under the terms and provisions of the
25 compact, the licensee shall complete a criminal background check performed by the
26 licensing authority in the state of qualifying licensure prior to entry in the compact and
27 shall:
Page 7 of 32
