UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1802
1 1. Satisfy one of the following two pathways:
2 a. Hold a valid current active certification through the BOC, or its successor
3 organization; or
4 b. If a licensee does not meet the requirements of 4.A.1.a., the following must
5 be completed:
6 i. An education program which is either:
7 1. At least a bachelor’s degree with a major course of study in athletic
8 training, or an equivalent course of study from a college or university accredited at the
9 time of graduation by CAATE, or its successor organization;
10 2. An academic degree from a college or university in a foreign country
11 equivalent to the degree described in subparagraph 1 of this subsection with a major
12 course of study as described in subparagraph 1 of this subsection that is accredited by
13 CAATE, or its successor organization; or
14 3. The substantial equivalent of the foregoing which the commission may
15 determine by rule.
16 ii. Successful completion of the exam administered by the BOC, or its
17 successor organization, preceding the date of the licensee’s application for licensure in
18 their state of qualifying licensure or the substantial equivalent of the foregoing
19 requirement which the commission may determine by rule.
20 2. Hold a compact qualifying license;
21 3. Have not had any encumbrance against any license or compact privilege to
22 practice athletic training within the previous two (2) years;
23 4. Be eligible for a compact privilege in any member state in accordance with
24 Section 4;
25 5. Notify the compact commission that the licensee is seeking the compact
26 privilege within a remote state(s);
27 6. Pay any applicable fees, including any state fee, for the compact privilege;
