10 B. The compact privilege is valid until the expiration date of the compact
11 qualifying license. To maintain a compact privilege, renewal of the compact privilege
12 shall be congruent with the renewal of the compact qualifying license as the compact
13 commission may define by rule. The licensee must comply with the requirements of this
14 section to maintain the compact privilege in the remote state. A licensee may apply for
15 and hold compact privileges in multiple member states.
16 C. A licensed athletic trainer must follow the scope of practice of the member
17 state where the patient is located. A licensee engaging in the practice of athletic
18 training in a remote state under the compact privilege shall adhere to the scope of
19 practice laws and regulations of the remote state. Licensees shall be responsible for
20 educating themselves on, and complying with, any and all scope of practice laws and
21 regulations state laws relating to the remote practice of athletic training, as applicable.
22 D. A licensee engaging in the practice of athletic training in a remote state is
23 subject to that state’s regulatory authority. A remote state may, in accordance with due
24 process and that state’s laws, remove a licensee’s compact privilege in the remote state
25 for a specific period of time, impose fines, or take any other necessary actions to
26 protect the health and safety of its citizens. Any member state which undertakes such
27 an action shall promptly notify the member state and the commission as specified in
Page 9 of 32
