1 the rules. The licensee may be deemed to be ineligible to exercise the compact privilege
2 by any member state until the specific time for removal has passed and all fines are
3 paid.
4 E. All member state disciplinary orders that impose adverse action against a
5 compact qualifying license shall result in deactivation of the licensee’s compact
6 privilege in all member states during the pendency of the order. If a compact qualifying
7 license is encumbered, the licensee shall lose the compact privilege in any remote state
8 until the following occur:
9 1. The compact qualifying license is no longer encumbered; and
10 2. The licensee has not had any encumbrance or restriction against any
11 license, compact qualifying license or compact privilege within the previous two (2)
12 years.
13 F. Once an encumbered license is restored to good standing as a compact
14 qualifying license (as certified by the licensing authority), the licensee must meet the
15 requirements of this section to obtain a compact privilege in any remote state.
16 G. If a licensee’s compact privilege in any remote state is removed, that
17 licensee may also lose the compact privilege in other remote states, as each member
18 state shall determine in its sole authority, until the following occur:
19 1. The specific period of time for which the compact privilege was removed has
20 ended;
21 2. All fines have been paid; and
22 3. Have not had any encumbrance or restriction against any license or
23 compact privilege within the previous two (2) years.
24 H. Once the requirements of Section 4.G have been met, the licensee must meet
25 the requirements in Section 4.A to obtain a compact privilege in a remote state.
26 SECTION 5. COMPACT QUALIFYING LICENSE
27 A. A licensee may only designate one license as their compact qualifying
Page 10 of 32
