5 H. If a member state takes adverse action, it shall promptly notify the
6 administrator of the data system. The administrator of the data system shall promptly
7 notify all member states of any adverse actions by remote states.
8 I. Nothing in this compact may permit a member state to take any adverse
9 action against a licensee or holder of a compact privilege for conduct or practice
10 occurring in another member state that was legal in the member state at the time it was
11 undertaken.
12 SECTION 8. ESTABLISHMENT AND OPERATION OF THE COMMISSION
13 A. The compact member states hereby create and establish a joint government
14 agency whose membership consists of all member states that have enacted the compact
15 known as the athletic trainer licensure compact commission. The compact commission
16 is an instrumentality of the member states acting jointly and not an instrumentality of
17 any one state. The compact commission shall come into existence on or after the
18 effective date of the compact as set forth in Section 12.
19 B. Membership, Voting, and Meetings
20 1. Each member state shall have and be limited to one (1) commissioner
21 selected by that member state’s licensing authority within 60 days of the member state’s
22 effective date.
23 2. The commissioner shall be an administrator or their designated staff or
24 current board member of the licensing authority.
25 3. The compact commission may recommend removal or suspension of any
26 commissioner from office.
27 4. A member state’s licensing authority shall fill any vacancy of its
Page 13 of 32
