4 D. The Executive Committee
5 1. The executive committee shall have the power to act on behalf of the
6 compact commission according to the terms of this compact. The powers, duties, and
7 responsibilities of the executive committee shall include:
8 a. Exercise the powers and duties of the compact commission during the
9 interim between compact commission meetings, except for adopting or amending rules,
10 adopting or amending bylaws, and exercising any other powers and duties expressly
11 reserved to the compact commission by rule or bylaw;
12 b. Oversee the day-to-day activities of the administration of the compact
13 including enforcement and compliance with the provisions of the compact, its rules
14 and bylaws, and other such duties as deemed necessary;
15 c. Recommend to the compact commission changes to the rules or bylaws,
16 changes to this compact legislation, fees charged to compact member states, fees
17 charged to licensees, and other fees;
18 d. Ensure compact administration services are appropriately provided,
19 including by contract;
20 e. Prepare and recommend the budget;
21 f. Maintain financial records on behalf of the compact commission;
22 g. Monitor compact compliance of member states and provide compliance
23 reports to the compact commission;
24 h. Establish additional committees as necessary; and
25 i. Other duties as provided in the rules or bylaws of the compact commission.
26 2. The executive committee shall be composed of five voting members, elected
27 by the compact commission:
Page 16 of 32
